headline: Goldman's Chen on China's Commodity Demand, Metals
summary: Trina Chen, Co-Head of Greater China Equity Research and China Basic Materials and Agriculture Analyst at Goldman Sachs, discusses country's commodity demand and outlook on metals. She speaks with Stephen Engle from the sidelines of the Goldman Sachs Global Macro Conference Asia Pacific in Hong Kong.

headline: Goldman Vice Chair Kaplan on Fed Policy, Dollar
summary: Rob Kaplan, Vice Chairman at Goldman Sachs and former Dallas Fed President, discusses the outlook for Federal Reserve policy and the impact from a weaker dollar. He speaks with Stephen Engle from the sidelines of the Goldman Sachs Global Macro Conference Asia Pacific in Hong Kong.

headline: Is Goldman Sachs (GS) Still Attractive After A 49% One-Year Share Price Surge?
summary: If you are wondering whether Goldman Sachs Group stock still offers value after its strong run, this breakdown will help you make sense of the price you see on screen. The share price last closed at US$929.72, with returns of 1.7% year to date and 48.7% over the past year. Over the last 7 days the share price has declined 1.4%, while the past month shows a 2.5% gain.
